The paper deals with an online bipartite matching problem with vertex weights, which is a classic problem in algorithmic game theory and online algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses randomized algorithms and perturbations, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper involves optimization and allocation problems, which are studied in cs.IT (Information Theory).
